title: Fix entered location from being reset when add a photo to a report
message:
Fix entered location from being reset when add a photo to a report

When submitting a report and attaching a photo to the report, after
going back to the report form, the location is updated to the
current location. Apparently, wrong value was being set when retrieving
the saved report. It was using the descript field instead. Fixed by
setting the right value for the location. Also the auto set is done only
when the location field is empty.

occurs due to duplicate categories being sent over. Had to clear the
vector that holds the categories of existing categories.

message:
Close #2408 - Fix offline report not uploaded when there is internet

Reports stored to be sent later to the deployment, are not sent when
the devices gains internet connectivity. This feature works with reports
not checkins. Found that, the code only sends offline reports when
checkin is enabled. Had to make it the other way around.
Send offline reports not offline checkins.

message:

deployment. It pre loads the text sent by the application to the

takes too long. Added a cancel button to the progress dialog to allow
users to cancel the dailog, when this happens, the unset report is saved
in the offline database for later submission.

title: Close #2247 unable to upload pics
message:
Close #2247 unable to upload pics

Reports fails to upload saying network is slow even though it's not.
This happens because during the upload process, the app thinks there is
a photo and it tries to upload but that fails causing the API to return
the wrong json response.

Fixed this by putting a condition to determine, if the photo really
exists.

The drawable which is used for showing a selected
deployment was named button_selected and this causes a different
drawable also named button_selected to show up. I renamed selected
deployment drawable to deployment_selected to make it show the right
drawable instead.

title: AddIncident: Improved location listening strategy
message:
AddIncident: Improved location listening strategy

The previous implementation would often listen to only one provider. For
instance, if GPS were enabled, getBestProvider would return "gps" for
both the low and the high quality criteria. Now we explicitly attempt to
listen to both the GPS and the Network provider, this way if GPS is
enabled, but the user is inside, we still have a chance of getting a
fix from the network. This also ensures that if, say, GPS is enabled
after the activity started, we'll receive updates from it.

In addition, the last known location is retrieved and displayed while
waiting for a better fix.
